galas, he's spoken
positively of these charities.

16:30.456 --> 16:33.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have called 326 looking for
evidence that
there were these personal gifts
from Trump

16:34.026 --> 16:35.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out of his pocket.

16:35.528 --> 16:39.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And between 2008 and this May, I
found just
one gift out of his own pocket.

16:39.365 --> 16:40.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That was in 2009.

16:40.466 --> 16:43.035 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It was for less than $10,000.

16:43.069 --> 16:47.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, when you ask
the campaign
about that, what do they say,
when you have

16:47.673 --> 16:49.642 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
asked them for evidence of the
giving?

16:49.675 --> 16:51.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID FAHRENTHOLD: They have
been very slippery
on this.

16:51.844 --> 16:54.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The last couple of days, they
have said Trump
gives tens of millions of
dollars away, or

16:55.014 --> 16:57.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he has given tens of millions of
dollars away.

16:57.149 --> 17:02.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But that answer includes gifts
from the foundation,
gifts of free rounds of golf
from his golf

17:02.588 --> 17:04.423 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
club to local charities.

17:04.457 --> 17:08.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They even sort of implied that
it might include
just the salaries that he gives
to his workers,

17:08.761 --> 17:11.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he's helping people by
paying them to
do work for him.

17:11.264 --> 17:15.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, they haven't broken down how
much Trump
actually gives out of his
pocket, and they

17:15.268 --> 17:16.702 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
seem to be determined not to do
that.

17:16.736 --> 17:17.703 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have asked for that a number
of times.

17:17.737 --> 17:19.272 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I have gotten no details on
that.

17:19.305 --> 17:23.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I know that
you will
continue to be reporting on
this.

17:23.542 --> 17:30.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
David Fahrenthold of The
Washington Post,
thanks very much.

17:30.383 --> 17:35.988 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DAVID FAHRENTHOLD: Thank you.

17:36.022 --> 17:39.825 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Stay with us.

17:39.859 --> 17:45.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": the
sugar industry's
influence over its link to heart
disease;

17:45.498 --> 17:51.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rethinking College to include
more Latino
men; and acclaimed author Ann
Patchett's foray

17:51.137 --> 17:54.240 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
into something closer to home.

17:54.273 --> 18:01.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: The European Union
has set aside
nearly $630 million for Italy to
cope with

18:01.480 --> 18:05.551 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
