across the
Mediterranean from Africa.

18:05.584 --> 18:10.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With so much public money
available, opportunities
to profit from the migrant
crisis are substantial,

18:10.823 --> 18:13.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as, it appears, is the potential
for fraud.

18:13.926 --> 18:19.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In June, special correspondent
Malcolm Brabant
reported on the Italian mafia's
use of refugee

18:19.332 --> 18:24.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reception centers in Sicily to
cheat the state
out of more than $4 billion.

18:24.670 --> 18:28.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The E.U. is now working with the
Italians
to try to end that.

18:28.407 --> 18:33.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As part of that effort, on the
Italian island
of Sardinia, authorities are now
checking

18:33.112 --> 18:38.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
into a scheme in which unused
and neglected
land was supposedly given to
migrant African

18:38.217 --> 18:41.454 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
farmers so they could become
self-sufficient.

18:41.487 --> 18:46.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From Platamona in Northern
Sardinia, Malcolm
Brabant and producer Alessandra
Maggiorani

18:46.192 --> 18:47.159 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
report.

18:47.193 --> 18:51.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: It's just
before sunrise.

18:51.530 --> 18:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's the start of the working
week.

18:54.133 --> 18:59.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we're heading out to the
land where these
50 or so African farmers are
supposed to be

18:59.038 --> 19:00.806 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
working.

19:00.840 --> 19:03.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the time of the day when
most farmers
out in the Mediterranean are
starting work

19:04.010 --> 19:05.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
because it's cooler.

19:05.411 --> 19:09.048 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They can get more done before
the heat of
the day really kicks in.

19:09.081 --> 19:15.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have been told that these
farmers work
from Monday to Thursday, so
let's go and see

19:15.154 --> 19:16.389 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
if they're there.

19:16.422 --> 19:18.391 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
