ALESSANDRA MAGGIORANI: I'm
saying that he's
finding excuses not to do the
interview.

27:15.801 --> 27:17.202 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Yes.

27:17.236 --> 27:20.105 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So these farmers, do they exist?

27:20.138 --> 27:23.775 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Do the farmers exist?

27:23.809 --> 27:31.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Luca Pintus insisted he wanted
to fight racism
and to help newcomers integrate
in Sardinia.

27:31.450 --> 27:35.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Migrants find it hard to leave
the island
because most are barred from
ferries to the

27:36.021 --> 27:37.823 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
mainland.

27:37.856 --> 27:42.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While migrants are a moneymaking
opportunity
for some, many Sardinians are
weary of those

27:42.094 --> 27:45.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
selling cheap goods on the
beaches or begging.

27:45.597 --> 27:51.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But people hawking wares in
supermarket car
parks have little alternative,
because a career

27:51.436 --> 27:55.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in local agriculture doesn't
appear to be
a realistic option.

27:55.374 --> 27:59.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant
in Sardinia.

27:59.077 --> 28:05.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Online, Malcolm
offers the
backstory of his peculiar
reporting odyssey.

28:05.450 --> 28:11.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's on our Web site,
PBS.org/NewsHour.

28:11.223 --> 28:23.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Now: how the sugar
industry paid
experts to downplay health
risks.

28:23.569 --> 28:27.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Researchers have discovered
documents showing
the industry tried to influence
scientific

28:27.839 --> 28:30.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
studies back in the 1960s.

28:30.576 --> 28:35.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Early studies had found a link
between sugar
and fat and heart disease, but
it now appears

28:35.347 --> 28:40.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the sugar industry paid two
Harvard professors
to point the finger elsewhere.

28:40.586 --> 28:44.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the time, it wasn't routine
to disclose
such conflicts.

28:44.590 --> 28:48.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Marion Nestle wrote an editorial
about the
latest research in "JAMA," "The
Journal of

28:48.527 --> 28:50.529 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the American Medical
Association."

28:50.562 --> 28:55.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's an author and professor of
nutrition,
food studies, and public health
at New York

28:55.701 --> 28:56.668 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
University.

28:56.702 --> 28:57.669 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome, Marion Nestle.

28:57.703 --> 28:58.904 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's start by a few...

28:58.937 --> 28:59.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MARION NESTLE, New York
University: Well,
glad to be here.

28:59.938 --> 29:01.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let's start with a
few definitions.

29:01.707 --> 29:04.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What was the Sugar Research
Foundation?

29:04.209 --> 29:11.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Well, this was a
trade association
for the growers of sugarcane and
sugar beets.

29:11.249 --> 29:14.286 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's new called the Sugar
Association.

29:14.319 --> 29:16.154 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So it's a trade group.

29:16.188 --> 29:23.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Its job is to promote the sales
of sugar and
to lobby to make sure that
nobody does anything

29:23.195 --> 29:26.832 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
regulatory to reduce the
consumption of sugar.

29:26.865 --> 29:27.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a trade group.

29:27.866 --> 29:29.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: So, yes.

29:29.668 --> 29:32.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when all the years when we
were being
told that fat and cholesterol
were the prime

29:32.437 --> 29:37.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
culprits in obesity and early
death and heart
disease, it turns out that sugar
also played

29:37.576 --> 29:38.543 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a big role.

29:38.577 --> 29:40.245 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Well, it did.

29:40.278 --> 29:47.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you look at the epidemiology,
at the time,
it was clear that both sugar and
fat were

29:47.386 --> 29:51.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
risk factors for coronary artery
disease.

29:51.289 --> 29:57.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But these investigators at
Harvard who were
paid by the Sugar Research
Foundation kind

29:57.195 --> 30:04.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of cherry-picked the data and
minimized the
problems with sugar and
maximized the problems

30:04.302 --> 30:06.138 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with saturated fat.

30:06.171 --> 30:12.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that was exactly what the
Sugar Association
wanted them to do, as the
documents show.

30:12.411 --> 30:16.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, the goal here
was to sway
public opinion, in much the same
way that

30:16.515 --> 30:18.050 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the tobacco industry did?

30:18.083 --> 30:22.154 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Yes, it followed
the playbook
of the tobacco industry.

30:22.187 --> 30:28.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The number one playbook rule is,
the first
thing you do is you attack the
science, you

30:28.960 --> 30:30.829 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cast doubt on the science.

30:30.862 --> 30:35.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Merchants of Doubt," the book
and the movie,
explain all that.

30:35.067 --> 30:38.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the Sugar Association was
doing exactly
that.

30:38.804 --> 30:45.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was trying to get researchers
to produce
research that would minimize a
role for sugar

30:45.143 --> 30:47.913 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and shift the blame elsewhere.

30:47.946 --> 30:53.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they were very frank about
what they wanted,
and the investigators agreed
that that was

30:53.218 --> 30:55.120 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what they were going to do.

30:55.153 --> 30:56.888 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Pretty shocking.

30:56.922 --> 31:00.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: If they could shop
for experts
for something like this, to find
someone at

31:00.592 --> 31:05.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Harvard who could tell them what
they needed
in order to preserve the
industry, how do

31:05.363 --> 31:09.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we know that hasn't happened or
maybe it has
happened in other nutrition
areas?

31:09.167 --> 31:11.503 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Well, it has
happened.

31:11.536 --> 31:16.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And The New York Times last year
had a big
investigative report about
Coca-Cola's funding

31:16.908 --> 31:23.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of thee Global Energy Balance
Network, in
which they had e-mails that
showed that there

31:23.148 --> 31:29.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were very close associations
between the researchers
who were doing some of this work
and executives

31:29.821 --> 31:31.690 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at Coca-Cola.

31:31.723 --> 31:35.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's very hard to get
documentary evidence
of this.

31:35.093 --> 31:37.195 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I do want to say one thing
about it.

31:37.229 --> 31:41.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's not a simple matter of
buying investigators.

31:41.900 --> 31:49.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These Harvard investigators, at
least one
of them, was really pretty
well-known for

31:49.574 --> 31:53.545 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his work linking fat to heart
disease risk.

31:53.578 --> 31:58.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so he probably believed that
that was
what it was, didn't think that
sugar was nearly

31:58.483 --> 32:01.586 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as important, and believed that.

32:01.620 --> 32:06.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So it wasn't as simple as the
Sugar Research
Foundation just saying, this is
what we want

32:07.025 --> 32:08.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and we're going to pay for it.

32:08.827 --> 32:11.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: When you say it's
not as simple,
I'm going to ask you a question
that is a

32:11.663 --> 32:13.598 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
little -- leans towards
simplicity.

32:13.632 --> 32:15.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What is the smoking gun?

32:15.300 --> 32:16.268 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is it sugar?

32:16.301 --> 32:17.803 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is it fat?

32:17.836 --> 32:22.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Oh, I think it's
both, because
both of them are nutrients.

32:22.707 --> 32:24.342 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And we don't eat nutrients.

32:24.376 --> 32:29.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most people don't eat sugar on
its own, and
nobody eats saturated fat on its
own.

32:29.114 --> 32:33.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We eat foods that contain sugars
and saturated
fats.

32:33.518 --> 32:37.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Diets are much more complicated
to study than
individual nutrients.

32:37.856 --> 32:41.159 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But that's really what everybody
ought to
be looking at.

32:41.193 --> 32:47.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And dietary guidelines tell you,
reduce consumption
of foods containing a lot of
added sugars,

32:47.132 --> 32:51.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and don't eat so much meat,
which is a major
source of saturated fat.

32:51.870 --> 32:58.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I say it's both, and you
have to always
take the number of calories into
consideration

32:58.443 --> 33:00.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
when you're talking about these
things.

33:00.245 --> 33:05.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: How skeptical could
consumers
be about these reports, which
every year seem

33:05.884 --> 33:07.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to tell them to worry about a
different thing?

33:07.886 --> 33:11.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: Well, I think
they should be
very skeptical.

33:11.957 --> 33:18.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first line of defense is
always to say,
does this research contradict
what I thought

33:18.263 --> 33:19.998 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I knew?

33:20.031 --> 33:24.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If it does, you want to be a
little skeptical
about it and wait for some more
studies to

33:24.469 --> 33:25.604 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
come out.

33:25.637 --> 33:28.039 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The science is cumulative.

33:28.073 --> 33:32.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nutrition science is extremely
difficult to
do, because people are terrible
experimental

33:32.844 --> 33:34.846 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
animals, and diets are so
complicated.

33:34.880 --> 33:38.683 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are lots of different ways
to put together
healthy diets.

33:38.717 --> 33:43.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we know that diets that have
a lot of
vegetables, that balance
calories, and don't

33:43.121 --> 33:46.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have a lot of junk food are
really good for
health.

33:46.124 --> 33:47.092 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We know that.

33:47.125 --> 33:48.493 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Marion Nestle, we
know it.

33:48.526 --> 33:50.462 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a question of paying
attention to it.

33:50.495 --> 33:56.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Marion Nestle, professor of
nutrition, food
studies and public health at New
York University,

33:56.334 --> 34:01.339 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thank you very much.

34:01.373 --> 34:06.478 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARION NESTLE: My pleasure.

34:06.511 --> 34:13.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to the second
installment
of our week-long series on ideas
to transform

34:13.551 --> 34:17.889 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
higher education for students
